      "subsections": [
        {
          "id": "getting-started",
          "title": "Getting Started",
          "order": 1,
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "heading",
              "text": "Introduction to SEB Server"
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "text": "SEB Server is a web-based application that allows institutions to manage and monitor Safe Exam Browser (SEB) clients during exams. It provides centralized configuration, monitoring, and control capabilities."
            },
            {
              "type": "video",
              "url": "/placeholder.svg?height=400&width=700",
              "caption": "SEB Server Overview (5:32)"
            },
            {
              "type": "heading",
              "text": "Key Features"
            },
            {
              "type": "list",
              "items": [
                "Centralized exam configuration management",
                "Real-time client monitoring",
                "Secure connection protocols",
                "Multi-institution support",
                "Flexible user management"
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "installation",
          "title": "Installation",
          "order": 2,
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "heading",
              "text": "System Requirements"
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "text": "Before installing SEB Server, ensure your system meets the following requirements:"
            },
            {
              "type": "list",
              "items": [
                "Java Runtime Environment 11 or higher",
                "MySQL 8.0+ or MariaDB 10.5+",
                "Minimum 4GB RAM (8GB recommended)",
                "HTTPS-enabled web server"
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "image",
              "url": "/placeholder.svg?height=400&width=700",
              "caption": "SEB Server installation wizard"
            },
            {
              "type": "heading",
              "text": "Installation Steps"
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "text": "Follow these steps to install SEB Server on your system:"
            },
            {
              "type": "code",
              "language": "bash",
              "code": "# Download the latest release\nwget https://github.com/SafeExamBrowser/seb-server/releases/latest\n\n# Extract the archive\ntar -xzf seb-server-*.tar.gz\n\n# Navigate to installation directory\ncd seb-server\n\n# Run the installation script\n./install.sh"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "configuration",
          "title": "Configuration",
          "order": 3,
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "heading",
              "text": "Configuring SEB Server"
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "text": "SEB Server can be configured through the application.properties file or via environment variables. Below are the key configuration parameters:"
            },
            {
              "type": "image",
              "url": "/placeholder.svg?height=400&width=700",
              "caption": "Configuration interface"
            },
            {
              "type": "code",
              "language": "properties",
              "code": "# Database Configuration\nspring.datasource.url=jdbc:mysql://localhost:3306/sebserver\nspring.datasource.username=sebserver\nspring.datasource.password=your_secure_password\n\n# Server Configuration\nserver.port=8080\nserver.ssl.enabled=true"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "monitoring",
          "title": "Client Monitoring",
          "order": 4,
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "heading",
              "text": "Monitoring Connected Clients"
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "text": "SEB Server provides real-time monitoring of all connected SEB clients during an exam. You can view client status, connection quality, and detected incidents."
            },
            {
              "type": "video",
              "url": "/placeholder.svg?height=400&width=700",
              "caption": "Real-time monitoring tutorial (7:15)"
            },
            {
              "type": "image",
              "url": "/placeholder.svg?height=400&width=700",
              "caption": "Monitoring dashboard with active clients"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
